postcontent:
Registered gunsmith and FFL offering transfers of all firearms between private parties.  
Price Structure is as follows: 
$25.00 for up to three firearms in one transaction.  Requires the longest wait time for the most restrictive firearm.  (two rifles and one pistol carries the 72 hour wait, three rifles is the 24 hour wait)
Each additional firearm, is $5.00  
If 5 or more within a 7 day period there is an additional $15.00 one time charge per transaction.
So  3 weapons $25.00   4 weapons $30.00  5 weapons $50.00 6 weapons $55.00 and so on.
All weapons must leave properly cased.  and secured.  If your transfer does not come with a case, you must either bring your case, or advise me and you will need to purchase a case prior to picking up the weapon.

Note those customers that spend $100.00 or more in gunsmithing labor services on the firearm being transferred, such as cleaning, new sights, get that transfer for only $5.00
Those customers that have spent $200.00 or more in the preceeding 12 months on gunsmithing services, get any transfer for $5.00 for one year of the original service.

title: For Sale:  BUYER BEWARE! Springfield XD-S semi-automatic handguns
postcontent:
Springfield Armory has a recall out for (nearly) all produced XD-S models handsguns, both 45ACP and 9mm. They are recommending immediate removal from service and return to the factory for warranty upgrade safety modifications. Delivery dates are now well into next year for models being shipped back currently. DO NOT BUY any XD-S that has not been warranty serviced, or BUY AT YOUR OWN RISK with the knowledge that you will need to complete the process yourself. 

Stock has been taken off the shelf for warranty service, and - as far as I know - new and/or modified stock is scarce, at best.

I have two XD-S pistols, one in each caliber, that have both been warranty serviced and returned. These little guys (or gals) are excellent shooters, but I do prefer my compact XD(M)s more, so if you're in the market for an XD-S that has been serviced already, take a look at my other listings and shoot me an e-mail and maybe we can come to a deal.

HEY GUYS 

We are now Offering custom frame work to the following
*polymer handguns
*magazines 
*knifes

If its polymer we can add a custom texture to it!!!! 

The process is called STIPPLING. 
This process is done my melting small devotes, holes , lines etc.. In the polymer this caused the edges of the holes,lines devotes to be raised giving texture.

This is a permanent alternative to grip tape or the grips that slide over the handle. Grip tape eventually wears down and can be an hassle to remove and install new grip tape. It also isn't very eye appealing on some guns especially on FDE or OD green guns at least in our opinion.
Doing this stippling to your weapon will give you flawless manipulation with it. If you think you can manipulate your weapon just fine under any situation try putting a small amount of soap and water on you handgun then try racking the slide or doing speed reloads.
